            <text>
                <body>
                    <div type="edition">
                        <div type="textpart">
                            <ab>+ Exemplar autentico. In nomine domini Dei nostri Ieso Christi.
                        Regnante domno nostro Liutprand viro excellentissimo rege, anno filicissimo
                        regni eius nono, per indictione quarta; feliciter. Omnium ecclesiarum
                        conditor Christus ipse nobis dat spem et certam habere feduciam, ut illut
                        quem a iuventutem nostra egessimus, per sacris et bonis operibus abluamur.
                        Unde ego <persName key="#Vir_devotus/vir_honestus #Vir_magnificus"
                            ref="#people/341"><name ref="Pertualdus">Pertuald</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Vir_devotus/vir_honestus">vir devotus</rs> considerans adque
                        pertractans animum meum, dum enim peregre non mea necessitatem, sed Dei
                        conpulsationem correctus habivi longioquo urbe, viduam, pupillum et orfanum
                        protegendum, illuc desiderium conplectus, liminibus beati Petri apostolorum
                        princeps Romane urbis devotum iuxta placitum Deo ad propria remeatus, queque
                        illuc Deo devotus sum ipso iuvantem, ut virtus permiset, opem perfici.
                        Idcirco ego Pertuald vir devotus offero Deo et tibi <rs key="#Churches"
                            >ecclesie</rs> beati <orgName
                            key="#Churches #Monasteries #Private_foundations"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/235">Sancti Arcangeli Michaeli</orgName>, quem
                            <rs key="#Private_foundations">a fundamentis fabricis vestibulis in
                            honore Christi domini constitui</rs> prope <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">domus cellula</rs> mea ubi cummanire
                        videor, quam et ad eius <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterium</rs>, id est:
                        curte cum fundamento ubi ipse ecclesia vel monasterio sitas sunt per loca
                        designata, fini <rs key="#Canals">fossato</rs> et trans fossato da occasum
                        solis, finis <rs key="#Cisterns/pits">puteo</rs> antiquo et strata publica;
                        terra pertenente <rs key="#Size">modilocum unum</rs>, ubi sibi abbas vel
                        monachi inivi consistentis <rs key="#Fruits/vegetables">ortum</rs> vel
                        pigmentarium havire debeat, una cum <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs>
                        <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Size #Fruits/vegetables #Cisterns/pits #Canals #Churches #Monasteries"
                            ref="#places/4">prope <rs key="#Cities">civitate</rs> ad
                            Valle</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Size">modiorum quattuor</rs>; <rs key="#Cereals">campo</rs> ad
                            <placeName key="#Size #Cereals">Quinto</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Size">modiorum quinque</rs>; <rs key="#Decima">decimas</rs> de <rs
                            key="#Wine">uinea</rs> et <rs key="#Oil">olibas</rs> quemquem havire
                        videor ad <placeName key="#Wine #Oil #Decima">Sancto Pancratio</placeName>;
                        et <rs key="#Decima">decimas</rs> de <rs key="#Wine">vinea</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Oil">olivas</rs> quem havire videor de proprio <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">peculiare</rs> in loco qui dicitur <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Cereals #Wine #Oil #Decima">Muriatico super
                            Sancto Petro</placeName>; similique <rs key="#Decima">decimas</rs> de
                        omnem lavorem meum, tam <rs key="#Wine">vinum</rs> quam <rs key="#Maiores"
                            >granum</rs>, <rs key="#Oil">oleum</rs>, vel de quot mihi Dominus
                        dederit inivi persolvere debeam; ad illas vero <rs key="#Wine">vinea</rs>,
                        quam nominatim decrevi ad designatum et devisum, decimas dare absque ista
                        decimas quod est mobile; ad illa vero in <placeName key="#Wine #Decima"
                            >Mule</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Wine">vuineas</rs>, <rs key="#Decima">decimas</rs> de virgario
                        adimplere debeas; et de gregis <rs key="#Horses">equorum</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Cows">armentorum,</rs>
                        <rs key="#Sheep">ovium</rs> seu <rs key="#Pigs">porcorum</rs>, omnia qui
                        nati fuerent a calendas ianuaria indictione quarta in ipso sancto loco, idem
                        decimas dare debeas; et <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >terra</rs> ad <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Object #Mention #Redistributive #Allocation_to_individuals #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/421">Arina</placeName>, <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Mention #Redistributive #Allocation_to_individuals"
                            >qui mihi a regia potestate concessa est</rs>, in integrum. De <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">casis</rs> vero: in primis, in
                            <placeName key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">Monaciatico</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">casa</rs> qui regitur per Sintarine
                        boulco cum omnia ad se pertenente in integrum; <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">casa</rs> in <placeName
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie" ref="#places/581"
                        >Ciceriana</placeName>, qui regitur per Maurello massario; <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">casa</rs> in <placeName
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">Capelle</placeName>, qui regitur per
                        Barinchulo massario; <rs key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">casa</rs> in
                            <placeName key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie" ref="#places/181">Monte
                            Colaccio</placeName>, qui regitur per Audolf massario; <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">casa</rs> in <placeName
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">Actiliano</placeName>, qui regitur per
                        Pettulo massario; <rs key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">casa</rs> in
                            <placeName key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie" ref="#places/580"
                            >Rasiniano</placeName>, qui regitur per Mauricio massario; <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">casa</rs> in <placeName
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie" ref="#places/556">Cicina</placeName>,
                        qui regitur per Deodatus massario; <rs key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie"
                            >casa</rs> in <placeName key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie"
                            ref="#places/91">Cornino</placeName>, qui regitur per Rodulo massario;
                            <rs key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">casa</rs> in <placeName
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">Rotiliano</placeName>, qui regitur per
                        Marcello massario; <rs key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">casa</rs> in
                            <placeName key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie" ref="#places/273"
                            >Roselle</placeName>, qui regitur per Teuduald massario. Haec istas
                        superius nominatas casas cum cultis vel in incultis, omnia et in omnibus
                        mobilia vel immobilia, quidquid ad ipsas casas pertenit, tibi predicte
                        ecclesie Sancti Arcangeli una cum aliis predesignatis rebus meis, quam inivi
                        pro anime me remedium per dotis titulo offerre visus sum, ab hodierna die
                        trado in integrum possedendum, ita ut sacerdus, qui inivi constitutus est
                        aut fueri, pro meis facinoribus Dominum deprecari debeat, officium Dei
                        peragendum, viduam, orfanum et pauperem consulandum, eginum et peregrinum
                        recipiendum, iuxta Dei preceptum omnium opem ferre non desinat. Et si quis
                        de filiis meis in ipso sancto loco Deo servire volueret, regulariter agere
                        nulla ei sit contradictio; quid si minime ex ligitimo prolis meus inivi
                        volueret Deo servire, et abbas qui inivi constitutus fueret de hac luce
                        migraveret, quem ipsam congrecationem sivi abbatem et priorem eligeret, ipse
                        sit in loco. Et nihil inivi meis heredibus potestatem habeas invasionem
                        faciendum, neque exinde aliquid subtragendum, nisi si a qualive homine ipse
                        ecclesia vel monasterio contra iustitia pulsatus fuerit, a meus proprius
                        heredis habeas defensionem, nam non menuetur. Contra quam dotalii seu
                        munusculi me paginam numquam me heredes meus adversus ipsam sancta virtute
                        aliquando spondimus esse venturus, sed omnia, sicut supra legitur,
                        inviolaviliter conservare. Quam dotalii et monusculi me cartulam <persName
                            key="#Writer"><name ref="Petrus">Petro</name></persName> nepoti meo,
                        dictante genitore suo <persName key="#Writer"><name ref="Petrus"
                                >Petroni</name></persName>, scrivere commonui. Actum <placeName
                            ref="#places/4">Luca</placeName>. Signum + manus Pertuald <rs
                            key="#Vir_magnificus">viri magnifici</rs> autori et conservatori. Signum
                        + manus <persName key="#Witness" ref="#people/342"><name ref="Sundipertus"
                                >Sundipert</name></persName> filio eius consentientis. Signum +
                        manus <persName key="#Witness" ref="#people/343"><name ref="Peredeo"
                                >Peretheo</name></persName> idem filio eius consentientis. Signum +
                        manus <persName key="#Witness #Vir_magnificus"><name ref="Ansualdus"
                                >Ansuald</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Vir_magnificus">viri magnifici</rs> testis. Signum + manus
                            <persName key="#Witness #Vir_devotus/vir_honestus"><name
                                ref="Aunefridus">Aunifridi</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Vir_devotus/vir_honestus">viri devoti</rs> testis. Signum + manus
                            <persName key="#Witness #Vir_devotus/vir_honestus"><name
                                ref="Radipertus">Radiperti</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Vir_devotus/vir_honestus">viri devoti</rs> testis. Signum + manus
                            <persName key="#Witness #Vir_devotus/vir_honestus"><name
                                ref="Teuderacis">Teuderisci</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Vir_devotus/vir_honestus">viri devoti</rs> testis. Signum + manus
                            <persName key="#Witness #Vir_devotus/vir_honestus"><name
                                ref="Audebertus">Autpert</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Vir_devotus/vir_honestus">viri devoti</rs> testis. + Ego <persName
                            key="#Copyist #Deacons"><name ref="Osprandus"
                            >Osprandus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Deacons">diaconus</rs> ex autentico fideliter exemplavi, nec plus
                        addedi, nec menime scripsi. + Ego <persName key="#Copyist #Other_clerics"
                                ><name ref="Ragibrandus">Rachiprandus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Other_clerics">clericus</rs> exemplar iterum fideliter exemplavi.
                        + Ego <persName key="#Copyist #Other_clerics"><name ref="Ermimarus"
                                >Ermimari</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Other_clerics">clericus</rs> de exemplare iterum fideliter
                        exemplavi. </ab>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div type="bibliography" subtype="editions">
                        <p>MDL, IV/1, n. 36; reg. MDL, V/2, n. 9; CDL I, 28, pp. 101-105; ChLA, XXX,
                    898-899 (scheda fatta dal n. 898, +N.4).</p>
                    </div>
                    <div type="bibliography" subtype="additional">
                        <p/>
